snippet.title: MinimPy
snippet.description: MinimPy is a desktop application program for sequential allocation of subjects to treatment groups in clinical trials by using the method of minimisation. Comprehensive reference help is available at: http://minimpy.sourceforge.net For those who have difficulty installing MinimPy an online version is available at: http://qminim.saghaei.net which is free. MinimPy has been introduced in the following article: Saghaei, M. and Saghaei, S. (2011) Implementation of an open-source customizable minimization program for allocation of patients to parallel groups in clinical trials. Journal of Biomedical Science and Engineering, 4, 734-739. doi: 10.4236/jbise.2011.411090. Available at: http://www.scirp.org/journal/PaperInformation.aspx?PaperID=8518
